rComments: I love this prof!!! She explains all the concepts really well. I learned more from her than I did my psych prof. Her assignments are very straightforward and is a fairly easy grader. I'm def going to be taking her again. She's my fave prof I've had so far!!!

Josee was very sweet and clearly cared for her students. She was an easy A, although at times her test questions were a bit ambiguous and so you had to work a bit for your grade. The class is small which is nice, make sure to participate and get on her good side (helps to show your face) and talk to her! She cracks small jokes and has a cute laugh

My favorite prof of the semester! I took her fls class for anthropology and honestly i learned much more for Josée than my anthro prof. Shes a really fair graded and very accessible outside of class. Id definitely take this class again and I am talking fls for psych with her next semester.

she takes attendance but the class is so easy. only once a week too. she is super nice and the activities we do in class is great review ( plus she makes it kinda fun with games ) midterms and final are open book
Best teacher ever. She is very caring about her students. The class is very easy and a light work load. Her classes help a lot in understanding course material for PSY 1501.

Very supportive, understanding and caring! The homework is a breeze and she gives clear feedback. Her teaching style is very casual and similar to high school french teachers (which i liked). She consults students on the final exam content and in class activities really help to understand the content. Would love to take her again! :)

Prof really cares about her students and does a lot to make sure they do well. I always enjoyed going to her class and I found it really helpful. It's an easy 3 credits for sure. Take this prof if you can, you will love her!

Professor Richer is so kind and patient! She is always willing to help you after class or at her office or via email! This course was an accompany course to PSY2510 and she made the activities easy and fun! I would highly recommend taking this course and she's a fair marker(on the easy side though)!

She is the sweetest and most caring prof, and she really cares about her students' success. The workload was super light and the tests and exams were pretty easy. She is funny and always answers any questions you might have.
Sweetest prof I've had. Really cares about her students and wants them to do well. The class itself isn't hard and there isn't a huge workload. The exam and midterm were fair.
Very sweet prof who is always willing to explain things again if you ask.
She cares about her students and wants for you to succeed .
Great prof that clearly cares about each student's improvement. There were a couple written assignments and a presentation, but nothing crazy. She really helped us understand the material.
So kind and her lectures are always well-constructed and super clear. There's a decent amount of homework and she's very accommodating. Would love to take another class with her.
Amazing!

For my class, I was not a fan of the lecture notes or the textbook. When it came to the midterm and exam, there was vocabulary and grammar questions there we had not at all covered in class. However, very nice and accommodating for all students.

I loved her! Her lectures are interesting and she works hard to engage the class. She is always available if you need to speak with her after class and is always willing to help. I would totally take her class again!
She is so sweet! Very friendly and funny too. Actually enjoyed going to her class although I didn't do as well as I had hoped to
It was the easiest class to show up to and get an A. Shes really nice and had a lot of fun taking the course.

I loved her!! She was always clear with what she was looking for. Always there for feedback if you need help or want to improve. She was super helpful with the answering questions in the actual content course and clarifying concepts talked about in class. Take a class with her if you have the chance!

Do not take FLS 2513 with her! Far too much material, and contrary to the other comments, you are not allowed to bring any notes into any of the tests for this course. The tests require you to be proficient in all subject areas that she covers... she will tell you material is on the exam, but it is not. Take this course with another professor!

The midterm and the final exam were open book and you could write exactly what was on the exam before hand and bring it to the exam and recopy it. The devoirs were easy and her lectures were just her reading off the powerpoint. Definitely would take her class again for the easy mark.

Very nice prof, very accommodating and helpful if you run into any problems or need clarification. Gets students' feedback/opinions for assignments and is willing to go out of her way to help you succeed in both her class and the accompanying course.

Super easy class, guaranteed A. The midterm and exam (both of them are open book) are literally 4 pages long and consist mostly of matching terms to their definitions. Prof is really nice, but maybe needs a bit more backbone.
